---
import "../styles/global.css";
const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>About — Preah</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A bit more about Preah — a university student, infosec tinkerer, tea enthusiast, and homelab enjoyer in Central Texas."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Crimson+Pro:ital,wght@0,300..700;1,300..600&family=Source+Serif+4:opsz,wght@8..60,300..600&family=Spline+Sans+Mono:wght@400;500&family=Newsreader:opsz,wght@6..72,400..600&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="wrap">
      <!-- ---------- site header ---------- -->
      <header class="site-head">
        <div class="brand-row">
          <span class="brand-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.0" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M10 2v2"/><path d="M14 2v2"/><path d="M16 8a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v8a4 4 0 0 1-4 4H7a4 4 0 0 1-4-4V9a1 1 0 0 1 1-1h14a4 4 1 1 1 0 8h-1"/><path d="M6 2v2"/></svg>
          </span>
          <a class="brand" href="/">Preah</a>
        </div>
        <nav class="nav">
          <a href="/">home</a>
          <a href="/blog">blog</a>
          <a href="/portfolio">portfolio</a>
          <a href="/about" class="active">about</a>
        </nav>
      </header>

      <!-- ---------- page header ---------- -->
      <section class="hero">
        <h1>About me</h1>
      </section>

      <!-- ---------- photo + intro ---------- -->
      <section class="about-intro">
        <div class="about-photo-wrap">
          <img
            src="/images/ireland.webp"
            alt="Preah in Ireland"
            width="160"
            height="160"
            class="about-photo"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="about-lead">
          <p class="hero-sub">
            Hey! I'm <strong>Preah</strong>, a university student studying cyber security based in the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Texas_Hill_Country" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Texas Hill Country</a>.
            I spend most of my time with my head down solving a weird puzzle that interests me, reading inbetween work breaks and on weekends, studying something intellectually stimulating, and traveling as much as I can. Mostly the beach :p
          </p>
          <p>
            When I'm not studying or hacking on a side project, you'll probably find me brewing a pot of tea, tending my homelab, traveling with my friends or fiancé, or getting distracted by a video game I've played a hundred times before.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ---------- the longer version ---------- -->
      <section class="block">
        <div class="block-head">
          <h2>The longer version</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            I got into computers as a young child. My brothers love technology and video games. I would watch my brother Karl play on his Minecraft server shared with his wife, and wish I could join. I eventually did, and played in unique ways: making my house random pits in the ground with only a bed or a giant house in the sky. I would make structures by studying mobs block by block and rebuilding them at a large scale, with house interiors for some reason.
          </p>
          <p>
            My brother Christer would play with industrial mods, and I would watch him build complex factories and automated farms. He would distract me all day with riddles to avoid giving up the PC. I would lie about how long I had been on the computer, and Christer would effortlessly pull up the amount of time the computer had been on to disprove me. My brothers did countless things like this that made me want to know more about how computers work and what I could do with them.
          </p>
          <p>
            This curiosity eventually led me to start learning programming in middle school, and I thought it was boring at first. I didn't have a project I cared about, and I didn't understand how to make the things I wanted to make. I gave up for a while, but eventually found my way back to it through game modding and cybersecurity. I found it much more engaging to learn by making things I cared about, and I was fascinated by the idea of being able to create something out of nothing but code. I also loved the problem-solving aspect of programming, and the feeling of satisfaction that came with finally figuring out how to make something work.
          </p>
          <p>
            Inevitably for me, I started hosting servers and learning Linux on my computers. By this point, I was the only kid left in the house and had my own computer. I started hosting Minecraft servers for my friends and family, and eventually branched out into hosting other things like websites, and self-hosted services. I loved the idea of being able to create and control my own little corner of the internet, and I enjoyed the challenge of learning how to set up and maintain a server. This eventually evolved into a full-blown homelab, which is still a work in progress but has been a great learning experience for me.
          </p>
          <p>
            My homelab is my sandbox. It's a small cluster of machines running a mix of self-hosted
            services, monitoring stacks, and whatever experiment I'm currently obsessing over. It has
            taught me more practical infrastructure knowledge than any course I've taken.
          </p>
          <p>
            My fiancé doesn't understand this side of me as much, but he loves the results: a fast, ad-free, and personalized internet experience, and a partner who is always learning and tinkering with new things. He is also very supportive of my interests and hobbies, even if he doesn't always understand them. We both share a love of travel and adventure, and we enjoy exploring new places together whenever we can. We love tea and often have a pot brewing while we hang out, and we enjoy trying new blends and flavors, especially when we started investing in gongfu tea. Overall, I feel very lucky to have such a supportive and loving partner, and by extension family, who accepts me for who I am and encourages me to pursue my passions.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ---------- interests ---------- -->
      <section class="block">
        <div class="block-head">
          <h2>Things I care about</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="interests">
          <div class="interest-card">
            <div class="interest-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Information Security</h3>
            <p>
              Log analysis, SIEM, detection engineering, and CTFs. I lean defensive but I think
              you can't defend what you don't understand how to attack.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="interest-card">
            <div class="interest-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M8 21h8M12 17v4"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Homelab &amp; Self-Hosting</h3>
            <p>
              Running my own services because I'd rather own my data. Also because it's a great excuse
              to learn networking, monitoring, and whatever else I decide to throw at it.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="interest-card">
            <div class="interest-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 8h1a4 4 0 0 1 0 8h-1"/><path d="M2 8h16v9a4 4 0 0 1-4 4H6a4 4 0 0 1-4-4V8z"/><line x1="6" y1="1" x2="6" y2="4"/><line x1="10" y1="1" x2="10" y2="4"/><line x1="14" y1="1" x2="14" y2="4"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Gong Fu Tea</h3>
            <p>
              A slow, deliberate way to brew tea that rewards patience. I'm particularly fond of
              aged oolongs and ripe pu-erh. It's meditative in the best way.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="interest-card">
            <div class="interest-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2 3h6a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v14a3 3 0 0 0-3-3H2z"/><path d="M22 3h-6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v14a3 3 0 0 1 3-3h7z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Reading</h3>
            <p>
              Mostly non-fiction: memoirs, theology, and the occasional dense technical book.
              Fiction gets in there too, as I have a huge soft spot for fantasy. See my <a href="/reading-list" class="card-link">reading list</a> to learn more (WIP).
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="interest-card">
            <div class="interest-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 11h4M8 9v4"/><circle cx="15.5" cy="10.5" r="0.6" fill="currentColor"/><circle cx="17.5" cy="12.5" r="0.6" fill="currentColor"/><path d="M17.5 5.5H6.5A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 2 10v4a3 3 0 0 0 5.4 1.8l.5-.7a2 2 0 0 1 1.6-.8h5a2 2 0 0 1 1.6.8l.5.7A3 3 0 0 0 22 14v-4a4.5 4.5 0 0 0-4.5-4.5Z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Gaming</h3>
            <p>
              I don't play new releases often, but I replay the same favorites obsessively.
              Skyrim, Minecraft, Spelunky, and a few others have permanent residence on my hard drive.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="interest-card">
            <div class="interest-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 13.87A4 4 0 0 1 7.41 6a5.11 5.11 0 0 1 1.05-1.54 5 5 0 0 1 7.08 0A5.11 5.11 0 0 1 16.59 6 4 4 0 0 1 18 13.87V21H6Z"/><line x1="6" y1="17" x2="18" y2="17"/><line x1="6" y1="13" x2="18" y2="13"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Cooking &amp; Baking</h3>
            <p>
              I love making food for people I care about. I bake bread, and I make elaborate meals for my fiancé and friends. It shows love and care, and it's also a fun creative outlet for me. I also brew my own kombucha, which is a fun process that allows me to experiment with different flavors and techniques.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ---------- gallery ---------- -->
      <section class="block">
        <div class="block-head">
          <h2>A few snapshots</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="gallery">
          <div class="gallery-row gallery-row--landscape">
            <img class="gallery-img" src="/images/beachside.webp" alt="Beachside view" width="400" height="300" loading="lazy" />
            <img class="gallery-img" src="/images/renfaire.webp" alt="Renaissance faire" width="400" height="300" loading="lazy" />
            <img class="gallery-img" src="/images/tower.webp" alt="Tower" width="400" height="300" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="gallery-row gallery-row--landscape">
            <img class="gallery-img" src="/images/beachdrink.webp" alt="Drink at the beach" width="400" height="300" loading="lazy" />
            <img class="gallery-img" src="/images/tikiparty.webp" alt="Tiki party" width="400" height="300" loading="lazy" />
            <img class="gallery-img" src="/images/birdwatching.webp" alt="Birdwatching" width="400" height="300" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ---------- footer ---------- -->
      <footer class="site-foot">
        <span class="foot-brand">Preah</span>
        <span class="foot-dot">&middot;</span>
        <span>{year}</span>
        <span class="foot-spacer"></span>
        <a href="https://git.preahs.com/preah">Forgejo</a>
        <a href="mailto:contact@preahs.com">Email</a>
        <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a>
        <a href="https://signal.me/#eu/7FQaEphPdhSrlUCPuqr8awsHVYUSiJ9CGua_YktOEMge3oIT-itMcKuS2r3k6x8Q">Signal</a>
        <a href="https://matrix.to/#/@preshavocado:snowberry.social">Matrix</a>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  /* ---------- about intro layout ---------- */
  .about-intro {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding-top: 1rem;
  }

  .about-photo-wrap {
    flex: none;
  }

  .about-photo {
    width: 220px;
    height: 260px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    border: 1.5px dashed var(--rule-strong);
    display: block;
  }

  .about-lead {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.8rem;
  }

  .about-lead p {
    font-size: 1.12rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 580px;
  }

  .about-lead strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .hl {
    color: var(--accent);
    border-bottom: 1.5px dashed var(--rule-strong);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .about-intro {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .about-lead p {
      text-align: left;
    }
  }

  /* ---------- prose ---------- */
  .prose {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .prose p {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .prose strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ---------- interests grid ---------- */
  .interests {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .interest-card {
    background: var(--paper-card);
    border: 1.5px dashed var(--rule);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .interest-icon {
    color: var(--accent);
    width: 1.4rem;
    height: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .interest-icon svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .interest-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .interest-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .card-link {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1.5px dashed var(--rule-strong);
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .card-link:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* ---------- gallery ---------- */
  .gallery {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .gallery-row {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  }

  .gallery-img {
    width: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    border: 1.5px dashed var(--rule);
    display: block;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .gallery-row--landscape .gallery-img { aspect-ratio: 4 / 3; }
  .gallery-row--portrait  .gallery-img { aspect-ratio: 3 / 4; }

  .gallery-img:hover {
    border-color: var(--rule-strong);
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .gallery-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }
</style>
